  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening financial transparency and developing the business case</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IABM is a maize seed producer and processes maize into maize flour and animal feed. The cooperative was registered officially in 2009 and its mission is to increase member&#x2019;s income through cooperative actions. IABM has 764 members and an additional 1,011 potential members, who both supply the maize grains to the IABM factory.

  



  













IABM has invested in a corn mill in 2016 which is currently operating at approximately 60% of capacity. The main activity of IABM was however the multiplication of maize seeds. The multiplication is done by members, whom sell the multiplied seeds to IABM. The cooperative then sells the produce to RAB. IABM can produce more than 300 metric tons of maize seeds (OPV) per year and can process 80 metric tons of maize grain into maize flour per year. Seeds which are not certified are being processed into flour. 













IABM expects to increase the maize yield in 2017 from 3.5mt/ha to 5t/ha. In terms of diversifying the sources of revenues IABM prepares to construct a storage for selling agro inputs and agriculture materials, construct a training centre and restart its mushroom tubes and mushroom production activities which stopped when the maize factory was implemented. IABM also targets to produce hybrid maize seeds. IABM wants to become a recognized actor in distribution of quality seeds, by ensuring respect of standards required by the Rwanda Agricultural Board, who is encouraging cooperatives to become certified seeds selling points. 

  















  













Agriterra and IABM have agreed to work on professionalizing the marketing activities of IABM and improve the production capacity of its members and the linkages with other cooperatives who can potentially supply their maize to IABM. IABM wants to expand its membership base and work on its transparency by getting external audits and presenting these to the AGM. To improve financial management, the staff will be trained on the new accounting software.



We aim to strengthen the transparency and to develop the business case of IABM</narrative>
  </description>
